description:
&lt;p&gt;**This post is subject to agenda for change banding**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Quality and Facilitator role is a key member of the team leading on our quality improvement journey. The post holder will play a key role working across all clinical areas to improve the quality of care in all key nursing and patient safety domains. The post-holder will also play a pivotal role in progressing work around CQUIN achievement and ensuring the quality of care is sustained and / or improved as a result.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have proven experience in implementing quality improvement initiatives and of engaging with the Multi-Disciplinary Team to develop and implement mutually driven schemes, as well as a passion for driving sustainable improvements. The post holder will also play a key role in relation to our newly expanded clinical governance team, contributing to the clinical incident “Rapid Response Team’ and embedding the learning from incidents with the clinical teams in a variety of clinical areas.&lt;/p&gt;
